<div id="review_3662975146" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3662975146" />
    <a title="Christian Fountain" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/108051766-christian-fountain"><img alt="Christian Fountain" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3662975146?book_show_action=true">Jul 10, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Christian Fountain" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Christian Fountain" href="/user/show/108051766-christian-fountain">Christian Fountain</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3662975146" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5328251935423062420">I read this book on and off for like 5 months, so I feel like I should say some things. Welty is an undeniably great writer. Place and setting are emphasized so much in her writing that you really do feel like youâre breathing the same air as her characters. Most of the time though, this means that not a whole lot happens. And what does happen is usually buried far beneath the subtext. Definitely do not read this if youâre looking for an exciting page-turner or anything like that. That being sai</span>
  <span id="freeText5328251935423062420" style="display:none">I read this book on and off for like 5 months, so I feel like I should say some things. Welty is an undeniably great writer. Place and setting are emphasized so much in her writing that you really do feel like youâre breathing the same air as her characters. Most of the time though, this means that not a whole lot happens. And what does happen is usually buried far beneath the subtext. Definitely do not read this if youâre looking for an exciting page-turner or anything like that. That being said there are a select few that I would describe as somewhat exciting, but those are sort of exceptions. As far as my personal enjoyment goes, I REALLY loved some of the stories, but quite a few were absolute slogs. Though, even when her stories are boring (they usually are) theyâre still pretty enjoyable most of the time. Itâs one of those cases where even if Iâm not into the story, itâs more due to me and my preferences than her lacking skill as a writer.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5328251935423062420" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


