<div id="review_1590442126" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1590442126" />
    <a title="Nicole" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/10836606-nicole"><img alt="Nicole" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1606321315p2/10836606.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1590442126?book_show_action=true">Mar 25, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Nicole" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Nicole" href="/user/show/10836606-nicole">Nicole</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback " href="/book/show/9600702-the-collected-stories-of-eudora-welty">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/10836606-nicole?shelf=short-stories-essays">short-stories-essays</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1590442126" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5117803662484962543">Read this for a book club, so I read through it fairly quickly. I had a hard time relating to the writing. I think I would have enjoyed it more if (1) I had had a handful of stories to focus on, rather than trying to go through them all, and (2) I had the time to research the context for some of the stories. I liked the last two stories the best (&quot;Where is the Voice Coming From?&quot; and &quot;The Demonstrators&quot;), as well as &quot;A Still Moment.&quot; </span>
  <span id="freeText5117803662484962543" style="display:none">Read this for a book club, so I read through it fairly quickly. I had a hard time relating to the writing. I think I would have enjoyed it more if (1) I had had a handful of stories to focus on, rather than trying to go through them all, and (2) I had the time to research the context for some of the stories. I liked the last two stories the best ("Where is the Voice Coming From?" and "The Demonstrators"), as well as "A Still Moment." </span>
  <a data-text-id="5117803662484962543" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


